Posts.Content: Jun 19, 2013 09:18PM Allagashmaggie wrote: My wbc has always been around 3.6 to 4.3. While doing chemo I got the neulastra shot so my levels went up into the 6 range. Now they are back to what appears normal for me - around 3.8. Doctors are fine with that. The rest of my blood work, platelets included, has been very normal. Had 6 rounds of chemo which ended February of 2012.
